The paper deals with the optimization version of a well-known computational problem, and presents a new algorithm for solving it. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and game theory (cs.GT).
